## Implementation Plan

### Problem
Three UX issues with `sentry issue list` after the #274 auto-pagination work:

1. CLI returns ~114 issues while UI shows 240 — mismatch because the Sentry API
   defaults to 14d when statsPeriod is omitted, but users expect the UI's 90d window
2. No feedback during multi-page fetches — with --limit 500 the CLI silently waits
   through 5 API requests before printing anything
3. Layout shift when event counts exceed 5 digits — COL_COUNT=5 uses padStart which
   does not truncate, so 123456 overflows and right-shifts all subsequent columns

### Changes

**--period flag (issue/list.ts)**
- Added `period: string` to ListFlags with default "90d" and alias -p
- Plumbed statsPeriod through fetchIssuesForTarget, fetchOrgAllIssues, and
  listIssuesAllPages options to all three API call paths
- nextPageHint includes -p when period differs from the default

**Pagination progress indicator (polling.ts + issue/list.ts)**
- Added withProgress<T>() to polling.ts — wraps an async operation with an animated
  braille spinner on stderr; reuses ANIMATION_INTERVAL_MS (50ms), formatProgressLine,
  and truncateProgressMessage from the existing Seer polling infrastructure
- Spinner message is updated via a setMessage callback, enabling live N/total counts
- listIssuesAllPages gained an onPage callback option invoked after each page fetch
- Both handleResolvedTargets and handleOrgAllIssues use withProgress; progress is
  suppressed when limit <= API_MAX_PER_PAGE (single page, no wait) or in JSON mode

**Count abbreviation (formatters/human.ts)**
- Added abbreviateCount() helper: raw string → right-aligned 5-char column
  values < 10K: padStart as before; ≥10K: K/M/B suffix with 1 decimal below 10×
  threshold (1.2K, 12K, 1.2M, 12M, 1.2B …)
- formatIssueRow uses abbreviateCount instead of padStart

**Animation interval (polling.ts)**
- Changed ANIMATION_INTERVAL_MS from 80ms to 50ms (20fps)
- 10 braille frames × 50ms = 500ms full cycle, matching ora/inquirer standard
- Applies to both the Seer polling spinner and the new pagination spinner
